Find out which package you should download to have a program:
	$ pacman -S pkgtools
	$ sudo pkgfile --update # Update pkgtools database

	$ pkgfile -b -v -- finger
	> extra/netkit-bsd-finger (0.17-5) : /usr/bin/finger

Order packages by size (aka using sort):
	$ ls -lh /var/cache/pacman/pkg/ | tail -n+2 | sort -k5,5hr | less
